    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "f1dfb56805ef2d4357d94b0c6b7530a59d49224ae7d23cd87ee1fa224f68200b",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Dirac and Erd\\H{o}s proved independently that when $l=\\lfloor k^2/4\\rfloor+1$\\[f(n;k,l)\\leq \\lfloor n^2/4\\rfloor+1.\\]"
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "f3bf8ae10a54b3c05b9525da095ddb3b0cd5671c616fc75e8d1a81a23825683b",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $f(n;k,l)=\\min \\mathrm{ex}(n;G)$, where $G$ ranges over all graphs with $k$ vertices and $l$ edges.\n\nGive good estimates for $f(n;k,l)$ in the range $k<l\\leq k^2/4$. For fixed $k$ and large $n$ is $f(n;k,l)$ a strictly monotone function of $l$?"
    }
  },
